            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHezekiah%20commanded%20the%20people%20on%20the%20wall%20not%20to%20answer%20the%20taunting%20insults%20of%20the%20field%20commander%20of%20Sennacherib%2C%20king%20of%20Assyria.%20Our%20flesh%2C%20or%20sinful%20nature%2C%20is%20always%20talking%20to%20us%2C%20trying%20to%20convince%20us%20to%20give%20up%20and%20give%20in%20to%20our%20impulses.%20For%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20lives%2C%20we%20will%20have%20to%20listen%20to%20the%20voice%20of%20temptation%20that%20is%20the%20%22opposite%20from%20what%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20wants%22%20(Galatians%205%3A17).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20discipline%20of%20godliness%20enables%20us%20to%20refuse%20to%20answer%20that%20voice%2C%20to%20simply%20ignore%20it%20through%20the%20power%20of%20the%20Holy%20Spirit.%20The%20people%20on%20the%20wall%20were%20totally%20submitted%20to%20the%20will%20of%20Hezekiah%20and%20refused%20even%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20field%20commander.%20Instead%2C%20they%20continued%20to%20think%20on%20Hezekiah's%20encouraging%20promise%20that%20the%20Lord%20would%20deliver%20them%20(Isaiah%2036%3A18).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhich%20voice%20in%20Galatians%205%3A19-23%20will%20you%20listen%20to%3A%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20flesh%20(immorality%2C%20hatred%2C%20jealousy%2C%20rage%2C%20envy%2C%20drunkenness)%20or%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20Spirit%20(love%2C%20joy%2C%20peace%2C%20patience%2C%20kindness%2C%20goodness)%3F%20You%20must%20learn%20to%20completely%20ignore%20and%20turn%20your%20back%20on%20the%20flesh%2C%20for%20%22the%20Lord%20is%20our%20judge%2C%20our%20lawgiver%2C%20and%20our%20king.%20He%20will%20care%20for%20us%20and%20save%20us%22%20(Isaiah%2033%3A22).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
